The paper deals with private computation over coded databases, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of Reed-Solomon codes and Lagrange encoding suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and distributed systems (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper involves the storage and retrieval of data from multiple databases, which is a topic in database systems (cs.DB). Finally, the use of polynomial computation and coding theory suggests that the paper may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC).
